# Checkpoint Persistence

After substantial work, append a structured entry when any of these occur:

- A bug root cause is confirmed
- A migration is added
- A PR is merged
- Runtime behavior changes
- A major UI or status semantic changes
- A new architectural rule is established
- A meaningful next step is identified

## Append-only event log

Create one file under:

`02 - Projects/GithubArchiver/entries/YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md`

(or `docs/ai-memory/seed/02 - Projects/GithubArchiver/entries/` when the vault is unavailable)

Do **not** rewrite old entries to change history. Add a new entry and set `supersedes` / `related`.

```yaml
---
id: incident-example
date: 2026-07-18
pr: 9
commit: abc1234
area:
  - search
  - daemon
type: bugfix
# decision | incident | migration | feature | bugfix | performance |
# refactor | test | release | technical-debt | research
status: open
supersedes: null
related:
  - pr-6
  - migration-030
  - search-fallback
title: Short headline
migration: null
---
```

Body: what / why / tests / remaining verification. No chat transcripts. No secrets.

Regenerate derived views (never hand-edit them):

```bash
npm run memory:timeline
```

Produces:

- `Timeline.md` — chronological
- `Current Status.md` — living summary
- `Project Digest.md` — single AI-priming doc
- `Knowledge Graph.md` — related-id map
- type indexes under `indexes/`

Do not write speculative conclusions as facts.
